channel.title: Compiling Errors of a Decompiled version of a client
channel.description:
Hello There, Sorry about the latest post, I've recently found the solution for that, and I've successfully created a RUN file!!! :D Now, the only error I've got is in compiling, I get the 100 error thing, and IDK how to fix it, I've even tried decompiling my own jarred client, and I've even got errors... If you can tell me how I can fix the 100 error compilation thing, then that'd be great!! :D
Thanks, Nael

item.title: Compiling Errors of a Decompiled version of a client
item.dc:creator: @matzie matzie
item.description:
@matzie wrote:

[quote=“Nael, post:7, topic:541008”][quote author=matzie link=topic=659876.msg4412484#msg4412484 date=1394334616]
there are no accurate decompilers for anything past java v5. Odds are there is broken logic if you tried decompiling it your self, and it will probably not decompile everything(correctly)
Download a decompiled client, not a client jar.
[/quote]

Yeah, but I’m currently trying to make a cheat client out of a known server out there… (so there’s not a decompiled version)
But when I run it, it works perfectly, when I compile, I get the 100 error thing…[/quote]
Either you have to understand java bytecode and do all the bytecode sections yourself.
or
Get another client as a reference, and hope they didnt change anything in the files.
or
Find an injection point into the client, where you dont have to decompile all of the files.

to my knowledge stream and client both have issues with decompiling, as do quite a few more. but there are several of them you can use as an injection point.

Read full topic
